    "body": "Thanks for reporting.\n\nIf you don't agree with Linus experiences with case-insensitive file systems, then various different ways to tackle this problem have been gathered here: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff/discussions/16440\n\nIn this case ;) I don't think it's a bug per se (cargo doesn't allow cargo.toml on sensitive filesystems)\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/issues/45\n\nWhat would be the repercussions to just naively compare any non lower-cased search name (like Cargo.toml) to their lower-cased counterpart (cargo.toml) without asking the filesystem again like pyright double-checks?\n* lower-cased search list: [pyproject.toml] (sensitive / exact comparison)\n* non lower-cased search list: [Cargo.toml] (insensitive lower-cased comparison)",
